PROMPT WRITING STANDARDS
ANATOMY OF A GOOD PROMPT
CODE  190CHARS
RULES
Start with the goal, not the method State constraints before asking for output — not after Include one concrete example if the format is non-obvious NU vague SC ("make it better", "clean it up") 
AGENT COMMUNICATION PATTERN
CODE  140CHARS
All inter-agent communication routes through Marcus. Marcus formats tasks as: 
PROMPT ANTI-PATTERNS
❌ "Improve this code" → ✅ "Fix the N+1 query on line 42 so it uses a single JOIN" ❌ "Make it look better" → ✅ "Match the Card component's border-radius and shadow to the design in Figma frame X" ❌ "Handle errors" → ✅ "Return { error: 'NOT_FOUND' } with 404 status when user ID doesn't exist" 